channel.name: Cooking Channel US
channel.title: Man v. Food
channel.desc: Casey Webb's appetizing adventures take him to Hoboken, N.J.; he munches on homemade mozzarella, takes a bite out of a bagel behemoth and comes face-to-face with a slice of pure fire.

channel.title: Bizarre Foods: Delicious Destinations
channel.desc: Andrew digs into the culinary treasures of Uruguay's capital city, Montevideo; he explores this meaty Mecca by highlighting slow-cooked Asado meats, thin-sliced steak sandwiches called chivitos and breaded and fried beef.

channel.name: Cooking Channel US
channel.title: Bizarre Foods: Delicious Destinations
channel.desc: Andrew explores the native dishes of the British territory with Caribbean soul, Bermuda; fish chowder, spiny lobster and cassava pie.

channel.name: Cooking Channel US
channel.title: Bizarre Foods: Delicious Destinations
channel.desc: Andrew explores the Southern-influenced food scene of Raleigh, Durham and Chapel Hill.

channel.name: Cooking Channel US
channel.title: Bizarre Foods: Delicious Destinations
channel.desc: Andrew Zimmern showcases legendary hotspots and diverse culinary treasures in Hollywood, Calif.; he highlights classic steak and martinis, Thai steamed whole fish, Armenian flatbread topped with minced beef, and Persian ice cream.

channel.name: Cooking Channel US
channel.title: Bizarre Foods: Delicious Destinations
channel.desc: From classic chilaquiles to Neapolitan pizza and Sonoran hot dogs, Andrew explores the multicultural cuisine of Phoenix.

channel.name: Cooking Channel US
channel.title: Bizarre Foods: Delicious Destinations
channel.desc: Andrew Zimmern heads to Mexico's Pacific coast to explore the local cuisine; in Puerto Vallarta, he tries marinated pork, traditional pozole and skewered mojo fish.

channel.name: Cooking Channel US
channel.title: Bizarre Foods With Andrew Zimmern
channel.desc: Andrew Zimmern traces the footsteps of Juan Ponce de Leon down the Florida coast; buccaneer-style bacon and chocolate anchovies to crab juice roasted on an ancient fire and powdered Key West shrimp.

channel.name: Cooking Channel US
channel.title: Bizarre Foods With Andrew Zimmern
channel.desc: Andrew samples Appalachian fare as he treks Daniel Boone's Wilderness Trail; fried, crispy peascakes and buffalo bone marrow to ham cured and aged in pillow cases.

channel.name: Cooking Channel US
channel.title: Bizarre Foods: Delicious Destinations
channel.desc: Andrew Zimmern reveals unique cooking methods and ancient recipes in Marrakesh, Morocco, including pigeon-meat pies, beef and lentil dishes cooked in bathhouses and whole lamb slow roasted in underground ovens.

channel.name: Cooking Channel US
channel.title: Bizarre Foods: Delicious Destinations
channel.desc: Andrew Zimmern heads to Madrid to reveal the most famous foods in Spain's capital; sweet and succulent roasted piglet to fried calamari sandwiches and tapas, Madrid transforms food into a true culinary and social experience.

channel.name: Cooking Channel US
channel.title: The Zimmern List
channel.desc: Andrew visits Nashville, Tenn., to take a bite out of Southern staples in the city that music built; Andrew stops by a festival to experience the perfect chef, food and music crossover, then digs into one of the best Sunday suppers in town.

channel.name: Cooking Channel US
channel.title: The Zimmern List
channel.desc: Andrew Zimmern travels to Branson, Mo., for live shows and comfort food classics; he finds unique eats at Silver Dollar City amusement park and country ham at Branson Cafe before grabbing dinner and a show at Dixie Stampede.
